    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen using `g<` to view the pager, the window that opens will cover the statusline. This is especially annoying when using `:set laststatus=3`.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI would expect the pager to appear one line above the statusline, if the statusline exists. I assume this would be a configurable setting, or perhaps it would only happen when `'laststatus'` is set to 3.",
